content:
I am currently working with Octave and I'm having trouble understanding how the plot function is working in the given context. I understand that the find function gives us the index of the data where y==1 and y==0. But I am not sure what X(pos,1) and X(pos,2) do in the function below. Can someone explain the workings of this plot function to me?

Code:
```octave
pos = find(y==1);
neg = find(y==0);

plot(X(pos, 1), X(pos, 2), "k+", "LineWidth", 2, 'MarkerSize', 7);
plot(X(neg, 1), X(neg, 2), "ko", "MarkerFaceColor", 'y', 'MarkerSize', 7);
```
